<div class="review-element js-review-element" data-reactions='{"icon":["1","4"],"num":70,"count":["69","0","0","1","0","0","0"]}'><div class="thumbbody mt8">
    <div class="thumb">
              <a href="https://myanimelist.net/profile/MapzOr" class="ga-click" data-ga-click-type="review-anime-reviewer-pic">
          <img src="https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/questionmark_50.gif" data-src="https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/questionmark_50.gif" class="lazyloaded" width="48">
        </a>
          </div>
    <div class="body">
      <div title="2:36 PM" class="update_at">Oct 31, 2018</div><div class="username">
          <a href="https://myanimelist.net/profile/MapzOr" class="ga-click" data-ga-click-type="review-anime-reviewer">MapzOr</a>
          </div><div class="tags"><div class="tag not-recommended btn-label js-btn-label" data-id="3" data-href="https://myanimelist.net/anime/1/Cowboy_Bebop/reviews"><i class="far fa-star"></i>Not Recommended</div><div class="tag preliminary">Preliminary
                <span>
                                      (13/26 eps)
                                  </span></div></div>      <div class="text">
                To start with, I want to point out that I don&#039;t understand the glory this anime gets. I watched it because of the &quot;No way!! You didn&#039;t watch Cowboy Bebop?!&quot;. This can surely ruin one&#039;s experience with a show. So please, when recommending an anime, don&#039;t hype over it so much, that raises the expectation of the watcher and he might get into this mentality where he is just trying to point out anything he dislikes. At least this is what&#039;s happening here with me.<br />
<br />
While I watch this anime, I feel like &quot;And?&quot;. Where is the story going? Most episodes feel like they aren&#039;t contributing
                  <span class="js-visible" style="margin-left: -4px;">...</span>
          <span class="js-hidden" style="display: none;">to anything. The characters are very well introduced, we get a good background of their life. Yes, I didn&#039;t complete watching it, but I believe that if the plot doesn&#039;t seem to be going anywhere after watching half the anime&#039;s episodes, then it&#039;s not worth my time. It felt like I&#039;m watching fillers.<br />
<br />
It&#039;s one of those three:<br />
1. It&#039;s very slow paced and everything becomes clear in the last episode/s.<br />
2. It has an open ending.<br />
3. Both 1 and 2, very slow paced and has an open ending.<br />
<br />
I always had this thought just before starting the next episode &quot;Maybe we&#039;ll get to understand something in this episode&quot;. Some people said &quot;Maybe you&#039;re not a fan of the classics.&quot;, I still don&#039;t know what &quot;the classics&quot; mean, and I doubt that will change my opinion..<br />
<br />
DISCLAIMER: This isn&#039;t a professional review. It&#039;s MY review.</span>
              </div>
